2 - Further Manipulation of the Data¶

The actual location, velocity and acceleration values of the objects are found via using Pythagoras Theorem and the ${x}$ and ${y}$ components,

In [6]:
def pythagoras(data,x,y,res):
    x = np.array(data[x])
    y = np.array(data[y])
    data[res] = np.sqrt(x*x+y*y)
    return data
In [7]:
x = np.array(['A-X (meter)', 'B-X (meter)', 'C-X (meter)', 'D-X (meter)',
             'D0-X (meter)', 'A-X Vel (meter/sec)', 'B-X Vel (meter/sec)', 'C-X Vel (meter/sec)', 
             'D-X Vel (meter/sec)', 'D0-X Vel (meter/sec)', 'A-X Acc (meter/sec**2)', 'B-X Acc (meter/sec**2)', 
             'C-X Acc (meter/sec**2)', 'D-X Acc (meter/sec**2)', 'D0-X Acc (meter/sec**2)'])


y = np.array(['A-Y (meter)', 'B-Y (meter)', 'C-Y (meter)', 'D-Y (meter)', 'D0-Y (meter)',
             'A-Y Vel (meter/sec)', 'B-Y Vel (meter/sec)', 'C-Y Vel (meter/sec)', 
             'D-Y Vel (meter/sec)', 'D0-Y Vel (meter/sec)', 'A-Y Acc (meter/sec**2)', 'B-Y Acc (meter/sec**2)', 
             'C-Y Acc (meter/sec**2)', 'D-Y Acc (meter/sec**2)', 'D0-Y Acc (meter/sec**2)'])

res = np.array(['A (meter)', 'B (meter)', 'C (meter)', 'D (meter)', 
               'D0 (meter)', 'A Vel (meter/sec)', 'B Vel (meter/sec)', 'C Vel (meter/sec)', 
               'D Vel (meter/sec)', 'D0 Vel (meter/sec)', 'A Acc (meter/sec**2)', 'B Acc (meter/sec**2)', 
               'C Acc (meter/sec**2)', 'D Acc (meter/sec**2)', 'D0 Acc (meter/sec**2)'])

trip = zip(x, y, res)

for i, j, k in trip:
    data = pythagoras(data, i, j, k)
